cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image recognition and classification of handwritten Chinese characters. It may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as Chinese characters are a form of written language. The use of machine learning techniques and deep neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on improving recognition accuracy through loss functions suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
